[3]
Date: Tue, 06 May 1997 09:15:18 +0930
From: "Hall, Robert (SAHC)" <Hall.robert@health.sa.gov.au>

For the discussion on the control of meningococcal disease, the
Australian National Health and Medical Research Council, which inter
alia advises on public health policy, has recently published:
National Health and Medical Research Council (Series on Infectious
Disease Control), Guidelines for the control of meningococcal disease in
Australia, October 1996, Canberra, Australian Government Publishing
Service.
It is available from:
The Publications Officer
National Health and Medical Research Council
Mail Drop Point 50
GPO box 9848
Canberra A.C.T. 2601
AUSTRALIA
While designed for local conditions, it should be useful to communicable
disease control staff in other industrialized countries.
--
Robert Hall
Acting Director
Communicable Disease Control Branch, South Australian Health Commission
Post: PO box 6 Rundle Mall SA 5000
Phone: (08) 8226-7177, (041) 982-6665
Fax: (08) 8226-7187
